15/04/2004
ANKARA, Turkey -- President Ahmet Necdet Sezer vowed on Tuesday (13 April) that Ankara would do everything in its power to turn the South Caucasus region into an area of peace and co-operation. 
Sezer made the statement during a meeting with his visiting Azerbaijani counterpart, Ilham Aliyev. 
Commenting on the Nagorno-Karabakh conflict, Sezer urged a peaceful resolution, based on the principles of territorial integrity and international law. 
The two presidents also signed a joint declaration of intent to enhance political and economic co-operation. 
(Anadolu Agency, Turkish Daily News - 14/04/04; Turan - 13/04/04)
